<big><b>Phrasal Verbs (Alphabetical Order)</b></big>

<b>Back away</b> : move backwards from something
<b>Back down</b> : stop defending a position
<b>Back up</b> : support or make a copy

<b>Break down</b> : explain; stop working
<b>Break into</b> : enter by force
<b>Break out</b> : start suddenly
<b>Break up</b> : end a relationship or separate

<b>Bring up</b> : mention a topic
<b>Call off</b> : cancel
<b>Call on</b> : visit or ask someone to speak

<b>Carry on</b> : continue
<b>Carry out</b> : perform or complete

<b>Check in</b> : register at a hotel or airport
<b>Check out</b> : leave a hotel; examine

<b>Come across</b> : find by chance
<b>Come back</b> : return
<b>Come in</b> : enter
<b>Come out</b> : be published; leave

<b>Cut down</b> : reduce
<b>Cut off</b> : disconnect

<b>Do over</b> : do again
<b>Drop off</b> : deliver; fall asleep

<b>Figure out</b> : understand or solve
<b>Fill in</b> : complete information
<b>Fill out</b> : complete a form

<b>Get along</b> : have a good relationship
<b>Get away</b> : escape
<b>Get back</b> : return
<b>Get over</b> : recover from
<b>Get up</b> : rise from bed

<b>Give away</b> : donate
<b>Give back</b> : return something
<b>Give up</b> : stop trying

<b>Go away</b> : leave
<b>Go back</b> : return
<b>Go on</b> : continue
<b>Go out</b> : leave home for social activities
<b>Grow up</b> : become an adult

<b>Hand in</b> : submit
<b>Hand out</b> : distribute

<b>Hold on</b> : wait
<b>Hurry up</b> : do something faster

<b>Keep on</b> : continue
<b>Keep up</b> : maintain the same level

<b>Look after</b> : take care of
<b>Look for</b> : search
<b>Look forward to</b> : anticipate with pleasure
<b>Look up</b> : search for information

<b>Make up</b> : invent; reconcile

<b>Pass away</b> : die
<b>Pass out</b> : faint

<b>Pick out</b> : choose
<b>Pick up</b> : collect; learn

<b>Put away</b> : store
<b>Put off</b> : postpone
<b>Put on</b> : wear
<b>Put out</b> : extinguish

<b>Run into</b> : meet unexpectedly
<b>Run out of</b> : have no more of something

<b>Set up</b> : establish or arrange
<b>Show up</b> : arrive

<b>Take after</b> : resemble a family member
<b>Take off</b> : remove; leave the ground
<b>Take over</b> : assume control

<b>Turn down</b> : reject; reduce volume
<b>Turn off</b> : switch off
<b>Turn on</b> : switch on
<b>Turn up</b> : appear; increase volume

<b>Wake up</b> : stop sleeping
<b>Work out</b> : solve; exercise

<b>Write down</b> : record in writing